"application": "IRAP",
"description": "IRAP is a tool for RNA-seq data analysis. It is written in bash and requires several other programs and libraries to be installed. These include: \n * **Make**: A utility for compiling software.\n * **Perl**: A programming language used for many tasks.\n * **Boost**: A collection of libraries for C++.\n * **Gnuplot**: A plotting utility for scientific data.\n * **R**: A statistical computing and graphics environment.\n * **Samtools**: Utilities for manipulating alignments in the SAM format.\n * **Picard**: A set of tools for manipulating and processing genomic data.\n * **Python**: A programming language with several libraries used for RNA-seq analysis.\n * **Java**: A programming language used for some tools.\n * **Mono**: An open-source implementation of the .NET Framework.\n * **Other programs and libraries:** The script also installs a number of other programs and libraries, including the following: \n\n * **BFAST**: An aligner for RNA-seq data.\n * **Bowtie1/2**: Aligners for RNA-seq data.\n * **Tophat1/2**: Aligners for RNA-seq data.\n * **HISAT2**: An aligner for RNA-seq data.\n * **SMALT**: An aligner for RNA-seq data.\n * **SOAPsplice**: An aligner for RNA-seq data.\n * **SOAP2**: An aligner for RNA-seq data.\n * **GEM**: An aligner for RNA-seq data.\n * **STAR**: An aligner for RNA-seq data.\n * **GSNAP**: An aligner for RNA-seq data.\n * **BWA**: An aligner for RNA-seq data.\n * **OSA**: A tool for analyzing RNA-seq data.\n * **MapSplice**: An aligner for RNA-seq data.\n * **Cufflinks1/2**: Tools for assembling and quantifying transcripts.\n * **StringTie**: A tool for assembling and quantifying transcripts.\n * **BitSeq**: A tool for quantifying transcripts.\n * **MMSeq**: A tool for quantifying transcripts.\n * **HTSeq**: A tool for quantifying transcripts.\n * **Flux capacitor**: A tool for quantifying transcripts.\n * **IReckon**: A tool for quantifying transcripts.\n * **Scripture**: A tool for quantifying transcripts.\n * **Sailfish**: A tool for quantifying transcripts.\n * **RSEM**: A tool for quantifying transcripts.\n * **Kallisto**: A tool for quantifying transcripts.\n * **Salmon**: A tool for quantifying transcripts.\n * **FusionMap**: A tool for detecting fusion genes.\n * **NURD**: A tool for analyzing RNA-seq data.\n * **FastX toolkit**: A collection of tools for processing FASTA/FASTQ files.\n * **FastQC**: A quality control tool for high throughput sequence data.\n * **Jbrowse**: A genome browser.",
